ion2star  aDie Rede von Gott im Buch Ben Sira wird vor alt- und neutestamentlichem Hintergrund beleuchtet. Der Tagungsband enthält sowohl übergreifende als auch exegetische Einzeluntersuchungen zur Thematik. Ein Ausblick auf die jüdische Wirkungsgeschichte rundet das Bild ab. Der Anhang bietet neben Einzeluntersuchungen auch diverse Berichte im Zusammenhang des Buches Ben Sira und eine Corrigendaliste zur Textausgabe von P.C. Beentjes.  aWhat is said about God in Ben Sira is illuminated against Old and New Testament background. This volume of proceedings contains separate overarching and exegetic studies on the subject matter. A broad consideration of Jewish influence throughout history rounds out the picture. In addition to individual studies, the appendix offers various reports relating to Ben Sira and a list of errata for the edition by P. C. Beentjes.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aGodxBiblical teachingvCongresses. 0aGodxWisdomvCongresses. 0aGodxWisdom. 4aDurham ‹2001›. 4aKongress. 4aSirach ‹Buch›. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh1 aAitken, James K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Eve-Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeentjes, Pancratius C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Teresa R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalduch-Benages, Nuria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorley, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDi Leila, Alexander A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEgger-Wenzel, Renate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb